parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal to engage can cause loss of braking ability, leading to accidents or near-misses, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes straight to the floor
the vehicle is unable to stop
the driver must use the emergency brake to stop
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake caliper can cause the brakes to overheat, leading to loss of braking ability, and potentially resulting in fires or accidents.
symptoms: causing the brake pads to overheat
the vehicle pulls to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause the brakes to lock up, leading to loss of control and potentially resulting in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: the vehicle pulls to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause the brakes to fail, leading to loss of braking ability and potentially resulting in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: the vehicle pulls to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake warning system can cause the driver to be unaware of brake problems, leading to loss of braking ability and potentially resulting in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake warning system fails to alert the driver of brake problems.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the fuel tank selector valve can cause fuel to leak or overflow from the gas tank, leading to a fire hazard, and potentially cause the vehicle to stall or cut off while driving, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: fuel pouring out of the gas tank
fuel leaking from the gas tanks
fuel overflowing past the filler cap.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause a range of issues, from minor inconveniences like faulty door locks to potentially life-threatening situations like fires under the hood or inside the cabin. These failures can lead to accidents, injuries, or even fatalities.
symptoms: sparking or clicking sounds from the wiring harness
and short circuits affecting various electrical systems.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded, especially if it occurs while driving at high speeds.
symptoms: often when coming to a stop or slowing down
requiring the driver to restart the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The separation of a wheel from the vehicle can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The wheel comes off the vehicle while driving
